Grammar Lesson #008:
"Have" and "Have Got" (Negative)

I have a car
I don't have a car

I've got a car
I have not got a car
I haven't got a car

You have a friend
You've got a friend
You haven't got a friend

He has a car
He doesn't have a car
He's got a car
He hasn't got a car

She has a house
She doesn't have a house
She's got a house
She hasn't got a house

It has a name
It doesn't have a name
It's got a name
It hasn't got a name

We have feelings
We've got feelings
We haven't got feelings

They have a surprise for you
They've got a surprise for you
They haven't got a surprise for you
